name: cosmosis-build-standard-library
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "cosmosis-build-standard-library" %}
{% set version = "1.0" %}
{% set version_for_conda = "1.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version_for_conda }}

source:
  url:  https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 98b71c4cc89b87b32f5ea7457a5b66a709a855e81ed1e0c448782bdec993060b

build:
  number: 0
  skip: True  # [(py < 36) or win]
  script: "{{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv"

requirements:
  host:
    - python
    - pip
  run:
    - python
    - cosmosis
    # For compiling standard librarymodules
    - compilers
    - {{ mpi }}
    - llvm-openmp  # [osx]
    - libgomp  # [linux]
    - bzip2
    - cfitsio
    - gsl
    - fftw
    - libblas
    - liblapack
    - camb >=1.3.0
    - make
    # for running python standard library modules
    - fitsio
    - astropy
    - cython
    - scikit-learn
    - fast-pt


test:
  commands:
    - cosmosis-build-standard-library && cd cosmosis-standard-library && cosmosis demos/demo1.ini && cosmosis-postprocess demos/demo1.ini
    - test -f matter_power.png

about:
  home: https://github.com/joezuntz/cosmosis
  license: BSD-2-Clause
  license_family: BSD
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: CosmoSIS Standard Library
  description: |
    This is a meta-package providing the dependencies for the CosmoSIS Standard
    Library, to be replaced later by a version of the library itself.
  doc_url: https://cosmosis.readthedocs.io/
  dev_url: https://github.com/joezuntz/cosmosis

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - joezuntz
